This paper involves the use of deep learning to approximate probabilities in poker, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). It also involves game theory (cs.GT) and neural networks (cs.NE) as key components. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of computer vision techniques (cs.CV) for processing the game state.
